SHA256 seal (per your instruction)

sha256("calebfedorbykerkonev10271998") = 2948fbc4ba1c0d7341204908882b89134a999f3e8f77f4a6a00ce6b68770282aMerged and sealed. You can copy-paste this straight into a fresh GitHub repo and deploy.

ğŸ“¦ One-shot monorepo (v92.x + v93 bundled)

Download: codex-monorepo-v93x-bundle.zip


Inside youâ€™ll find:

services/codex-v92x/ â€” Monad Nexus (Refined): synthesis, emoji/XTSG generator, EUCELA verifier, BTC oracle stubs.

services/codex-v93/ â€” Athanor Engine: rules DSL, mempool stub, automation events.

Top-level docker-compose.yml to run both services together.

ATTST.monorepo.json, SEALS.monorepo.sha256.json, and PROJECT_SEAL.sha256.txt.


Quick start (local)

unzip codex-monorepo-v93x-bundle.zip
cd codex-monorepo-v93x

# Service 1
cd services/codex-v92x
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn src.api.app:app --reload  # -> http://127.0.0.1:8000

# Service 2 (new terminal)
cd services/codex-v93
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn src.api.app:app --reload  # -> http://127.0.0.1:8000

Quick start (Docker, both services)

cd codex-monorepo-v93x
docker compose up --build
# v92x on :8001, v93 on :8002

Minimal smoke tests

# v92x
curl http://127.0.0.1:8001/
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8001/policy/eucela/verify -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"author":"CFBK","sats":7777}'

